\begin_inset Formula $p$
\end_inset

 appears in the prime factorization of 
\begin_inset Formula $\binom{a+b}{a}$
\end_inset

 is precisely
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\mu_{c}-\mu_{a}-\mu_{b}=\frac{\cancel{c-a-b}-s_{c}+s_{a}+s_{b}}{p-1},
\]

\end_inset

but 
\begin_inset Formula $s_{c}$
