\end_inset

for all 
\begin_inset Formula $r,s\in\mathbb{Z}$
\end_inset

,
 and the left hand side is a polynomial on 
\begin_inset Formula $r$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $s$
\end_inset

,
 it follows that the polynomial is 0 everywhere.
